President Muhammadu Buhari and Governors, who are members of the All Progressives Congress (APC), are currently meeting at the State House, Abuja. The meeting started with the arrival of the president to the council chamber of the State House at 11:37am. The governors in attendance are of; Yobe, Osun, Ekiti, Edo, Plateau, Niger, Kogi, Borno, Nasarawa and Ogun states. The deputy governors of Kaduna and Katsina states are also attending the meeting. Our correspondent reports that the meeting tagged: “Audience with APC governors” is holding 21 days after the president was sworn in for second term. The president is yet to make any appointment since he was sworn in, even as scheming for his cabinet had intensified in states. Details soon. Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin